	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_REDCOAT">
			<Text>Redcoat</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_REDCOAT_TEXT">
			<Text>Redcoat was the historical term for soliders in the British army, which wore distinct red uniforms. Originally a term of insult orchestrated by the French to suggest the brutality of the British army, it became a term of endearment and the uniform remains apart of the ceremonial guard today, despite the British army having moved toward scarlet uniforms in the 1870s.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_REDCOAT_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Redcoat is an English replacement for the Rifleman. It gains a combat bonus when fighting in foreign territory, making it great for war into exotic lands.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_HELP_REDCOAT">
			<Text>+20% Combat Strength in Foreign Territory.</Text>
		</Row>
